TY  - JOUR
T1  - Further Remarks on Retrospective Accounts on Organizational and Strategic Management Research
AU  - Golden, Brian R.
Y1  - 1997/10/01
PY  - 1997
DA  - 1997/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256935
DO  - 10.5465/256935
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1243
EP  - 1252
VL  - 40
IS  - 5
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Miller, Cardinal, and Glick (1997) challenged the conclusions in Golden (1992b), which examined the use of retrospective data in strategic management research. Further, the authors suggest that my findings have led many other researchers to avoid the use of retrospective data. The present note suggests recent researchers have not entirely avoided retrospective data but have perhaps added precautions when using such data. I also suggest that Miller and colleagues did not fully represent important aspects of my research and inappropriately compare my study with others.
AB  - Miller, Cardinal, and Glick (1997) challenged the conclusions in Golden (1992b), which examined the use of retrospective data in strategic management research. Further, the authors suggest that my findings have led many other researchers to avoid the use of retrospective data. The present note suggests recent researchers have not entirely avoided retrospective data but have perhaps added precautions when using such data. I also suggest that Miller and colleagues did not fully represent important aspects of my research and inappropriately compare my study with others.
